WEBVTT

00:02.286 --> 00:04.011
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:04.340 --> 00:06.166
So is it still there?

00:06.191 --> 00:07.221
It's still there.

00:07.246 --> 00:09.552
Congratulations. You're
officially six weeks along.

00:09.586 --> 00:10.838
Is it always like this?

00:10.863 --> 00:13.206
It gets worse when
there's a lot going on.

00:13.231 --> 00:15.519
One of the things that helps me
when I'm feeling stressed, though,

00:15.543 --> 00:18.225
- is running.
- She told you what I said?

00:20.613 --> 00:22.247
<i>Let's all raise a glass</i>

00:22.282 --> 00:24.716
to my unemployed 28-year-old son.

00:24.894 --> 00:27.886
<i>My life,</i> before I met
you, Bec, it wasn't great.

00:27.910 --> 00:30.724
<i>I just tried to get away
from my father.</i>

00:30.749 --> 00:32.323
I've been working my ass off,

00:32.348 --> 00:34.621
and I am finally on the brink
of something special,

00:34.646 --> 00:37.014
<i>and I will be damned
if I let this stupid knee</i>

00:37.048 --> 00:38.856
<i>destroy another one of my dreams.</i>

00:40.819 --> 00:42.787
Stop!

00:42.821 --> 00:44.482
- Stop it, it's mine!
- Why can't you get it?

00:44.506 --> 00:45.465
It's mine!

00:45.490 --> 00:47.443
- You're gonna keep the boys safe?
- Oh, yeah. I will.

00:47.467 --> 00:49.326
- You have moisturizer for Randall?
- Check.

00:49.350 --> 00:50.920
And remember,
Kevin's afraid of bears.

00:50.944 --> 00:52.411
- So am I.
- Okay.

00:52.419 --> 00:53.963
Uh, the number for
the campground's by...

00:53.987 --> 00:55.354
By the phone in the kitchen.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.089
- I told you that already.
- Three times.

00:57.124 --> 00:59.018
- Okay.
- You really think that this trip

00:59.043 --> 01:00.825
is gonna help the boys get along better?

01:01.301 --> 01:02.022
I do.

01:02.047 --> 01:04.260
- Because Kevin can be so...
- Yep.

01:04.286 --> 01:06.183
And Randall is just
only trying to help.

01:06.208 --> 01:07.706
I know, baby. It's gonna be great.

01:07.731 --> 01:09.382
Look, camping's all about teamwork.

01:09.435 --> 01:11.079
Do you remember how the
Steelers were a wreck

01:11.103 --> 01:12.869
at the start of the '79 season?

01:14.017 --> 01:15.737
You're gonna Chuck Noll the boys?

01:15.762 --> 01:17.011
I'm gonna Chuck Noll the boys.

01:17.011 --> 01:18.883
- Okay. Good luck.
- Okay.

01:18.914 --> 01:20.885
- I'm gonna tell Mom or Dad!
- Stop!

01:20.910 --> 01:23.344
- Go get 'em, Coach.
- Oh!

01:24.547 --> 01:25.750
Oh, do you guys hear that?

01:25.775 --> 01:26.844
Do you know that sound?

01:27.095 --> 01:29.596
That is the call of the wild.

01:29.631 --> 01:31.141
- Hey, Kate!
- Come on, hop in the car.

01:31.165 --> 01:32.851
Your brothers are leaving.
Come say good-bye.

01:32.875 --> 01:34.635
Randall, put that up front for me.

01:34.669 --> 01:36.270
Thank you. Kev, here.

01:36.304 --> 01:38.438
We are gonna have the
best girl's day ever.

01:38.473 --> 01:39.873
- We are?
- Yeah.

01:39.907 --> 01:42.238
Can you say movies and manicures?

01:42.727 --> 01:44.578
I think the first thing we'll want to do

01:44.612 --> 01:47.352
- is set up the tent when we get there.
- Ugh!

01:50.703 --> 01:52.485
- Backseat.
- I'm already up here, Dad.

01:52.510 --> 01:54.236
Get in the backseat with your brother.

01:56.313 --> 01:58.076
Hey, and no Game Boy.

01:58.123 --> 01:59.038
What?

01:59.839 --> 02:02.105
Come on. There is no
Mario out in the wild.

02:03.239 --> 02:05.207
- Bye, guys. Good luck!
- Bye.

