and it's all cued up.

36:44.232 --> 36:46.265
Uh, he's just gonna
charge it a little for me.

36:46.290 --> 36:47.828
Those batteries, they go...

36:47.907 --> 36:50.131
So he's just gonna charge it.

36:51.921 --> 36:53.478
- Toby?
- What?

36:54.041 --> 36:55.222
- Tobias?
- I'm sorry.

36:55.247 --> 36:57.749
I'm sorry, I... had to.

37:03.383 --> 37:04.706
How's it going? We're pregnant.

37:04.731 --> 37:05.945
Hi there. We're having a baby.

37:24.546 --> 37:26.289
All right, we can go now.

38:19.114 --> 38:20.743
Are these cold yet?

38:27.817 --> 38:29.486
You guys have one of those for me?

38:30.333 --> 38:31.394
Here.

38:31.787 --> 38:33.499
Hand me that bag.

38:39.165 --> 38:40.611
You better spin that one.

38:41.734 --> 38:43.010
Ooh! Ooh!

38:53.532 --> 38:54.914
Jack's not coming.

39:18.906 --> 39:20.221
Just so you know,

39:21.006 --> 39:23.995
your son is a great father

39:24.020 --> 39:26.814
<i>and provider and husband.</i>

39:28.019 --> 39:30.025
<i>You think you screwed
him up, but you didn't.</i>

39:30.545 --> 39:32.556
<i>You only made him stronger.</i>

39:54.204 --> 39:55.273
- Hi!
- Hi!

39:55.298 --> 39:56.671
I missed you.

39:58.105 --> 39:59.210
Hey, bud.

39:59.349 --> 40:00.782
- It was so awesome.
- Yeah?

40:00.949 --> 40:02.665
Gonna get you!

40:32.835 --> 40:36.006
Hi, um, this is Kevin Pearson,
the actor.

40:36.031 --> 40:38.834
Listen, I was, um, a patient
of Dr. Miller's

40:38.867 --> 40:40.345
a couple years ago.

40:42.097 --> 40:43.598
I'm in a lot of pain,

40:43.631 --> 40:47.723
so, uh, call me back, please.

41:00.903 --> 41:02.204
Where are we?

